    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-28T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-28T07:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/790: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-28T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 28, 1918—12 [noon.]</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 28—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>196. Your number 77, November 26, 8 p.m. I took this matter up with Hoover very
                    hurriedly as he was about to leave for Brussels. Hoover did not seem to think it
                    would be wise to move along lines you suggested at present time. I will take it
                    up with him later and advise you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
